#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn36.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Sagāthāvagga "
msgstr "1. With Verses "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Pātālasutta "
msgstr "4. The Abyss "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn36.4:1.1"
msgid "“Assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano yaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when an uneducated ordinary person says that "

# NOTE: BB translates as “bottomless abyss”, which overlooks the connotation with an underworld, found both in the commentary and the sanskrit. http://sanskritdictionary.com/?iencoding=iast&q=p%C4%81t%C4%81la&lang=sans&action=Search
msgctxt "sn36.4:1.2"
msgid "‘atthi mahāsamudde pātālo’ti. "
msgstr "there’s a hellish abyss under the ocean, "

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano asantaṃ avijjamānaṃ evaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati: "
msgstr "they’re speaking of something that doesn’t exist. "

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.4"
msgid "‘atthi mahāsamudde pātālo’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.4:1.5"
msgid "Sārīrikānaṃ kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhānaṃ vedanānaṃ adhivacanaṃ yadidaṃ ‘pātālo’ti. "
msgstr "‘Hellish abyss’ is a term for painful physical feelings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.4:1.6"
msgid "Assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano sārīrikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "When an uneducated ordinary person experiences painful physical feelings they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion. "

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘assutavā puthujjano pātāle na paccuṭṭhāsi, gādhañca nājjhagā’. "
msgstr "They’re called an uneducated ordinary person who hasn’t stood up in the hellish abyss and has gained no footing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.4:1.8"
msgid "Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sārīrikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno neva socati, na kilamati, na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "When an educated noble disciple experiences painful physical feelings they don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion. "

msgctxt "sn36.4:1.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘sutavā ariyasāvako pātāle paccuṭṭhāsi, gādhañca ajjhagā’ti. "
msgstr "They’re called an educated noble disciple who has stood up in the hellish abyss and gained a footing. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.1"
msgid "Yo etā nādhivāseti, "
msgstr "If you can’t abide "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.2"
msgid "uppannā vedanā dukhā; "
msgstr "those painful physical feelings "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.3"
msgid "Sārīrikā pāṇaharā, "
msgstr "that arise and sap your vitality; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:2.4"
msgid "yāhi phuṭṭho pavedhati. "
msgstr "if you tremble at their touch, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.1"
msgid "Akkandati parodati, "
msgstr "weeping and wailing, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.2"
msgid "dubbalo appathāmako; "
msgstr "a weakling lacking strength—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.3"
msgid "Na so pātāle paccuṭṭhāsi, "
msgstr "you won’t stand up in the hellish abyss "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:3.4"
msgid "atho gādhampi nājjhagā. "
msgstr "and gain a footing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.207, sc4
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.1"
msgid "Yo cetā adhivāseti, "
msgstr "If you can abide "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.2"
msgid "uppannā vedanā dukhā; "
msgstr "those painful physical feelings "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.3"
msgid "Sārīrikā pāṇaharā, "
msgstr "that arise and sap your vitality; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.4"
msgid "yāhi phuṭṭho na vedhati; "
msgstr "if you don’t tremble at their touch—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.5"
msgid "Sa ve pātāle paccuṭṭhāsi, "
msgstr "you stand up in the hellish abyss "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.6"
msgid "atho gādhampi ajjhagā”ti. "
msgstr "and gain a footing.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.4:4.7"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
